				$LF
			]p
			[p 
				[b 
					"Upload
				]b
				$LF
			]p
			[ul 
				[li 
					"Encoders are able to 
					[a class=intlink href=/EncoderGuidelines/TASVideosChannel 
						"upload to our YouTube Channel
					]a
					".
					$LF
				]li
				[li 
					"In order to ease uploading in general, try using our 
					[a class=intlink href=/YoutubeUploader 
						"YouTube Uploader
					]a
					".
					$LF
				]li
			]ul
			[p 
				[b 
					"Link
				]b
				$LF
			]p
			[ul 
				[li 
					"The site now fully supports YouTube playlists in most of its modules, so please link to the playlist.
					$LF
				]li
			]ul
		]div
		[div class=tab-pane fade id=tabs-3371-1 
			[p 
				[b 
					"Uploading
				]b
				$LF
			]p
			[ul 
				[li 
					"Dailymotion has no batch uploading.  Each segment will have to be done one at a time.
					$LF
				]li
			]ul
			[p 
				[b 
					"Group
				]b
				$LF
			]p
			[ul 
				[li 
					"Add to the group "Tool Assisted Speedruns"
					$LF
				]li
			]ul
			[p 
				[b 
					"Obsoletion
				]b
				$LF
			]p
			[ul 
				[li 
					"If the movie obsoletes a published movie, remove the movie from the Tool Assisted Speedruns group and add it to the TASVideos-obsoletions group.
					$LF
				]li
			]ul
			[p 
				[b 
					"Link
				]b
				$LF
			]p
			[ul 
				[li 
					" For segmented videos, link to Part 1.
					$LF
				]li
			]ul
			[p 
				[b 
					"Motion Maker
				]b
				$LF
			]p
			[ul 
				[li 
					"Although not required, it is 
					[em 
						"highly recommended
					]em
					" that you obtain a 
					[em 
						"Motion Maker
					]em
					" account and upload TAS's as 
					[em 
						"Creative Content
					]em
					". If you do obtain a 
					[em 
						"Motion Maker
					]em
					" account, you will be able to upload videos longer than 60 minutes without splitting them, assuming you put them under the 
					[em 
						"Creative Content
					]em
					" label. A 
					[em 
						"Creative Content
					]em
					" video can also be uploaded in 720p 
					[a class=intlink href=/EncodingGuide/HighDefinition 
						"High Definition
					]a
					".
					$LF
					[ul 
						[li 
							"If you get rejected 
							[em 
								"Motion Maker
							]em
							" status or a video gets rejected as 
							[em 
								"Creative Content
							]em
							" contact 
							"[mailto:paul.hernandez@dailymotion.com]
							" to rectify the situation.
							$LF
						]li
					]ul
				]li
			]ul
		]div
		[div class=tab-pane fade id=tabs-3371-2 
			[p 
				[b 
					"Uploading
				]b
				$LF
			]p
			[ul 
				[li 
					"Upload the files using batch upload.  Viddler's simple upload won't allow MKV files!
					$LF
				]li
			]ul
			[p 
				[b 
					"Group
				]b
				$LF
			]p
			[ul 
				[li 
					"Add to the TASVideos.org group.
					$LF
				]li
			]ul
			[p 
				[b 
					"Obsoletion
				]b
				$LF
			]p
			[ul 
				[li 
					"If the movie obsoletes a published movie, remove the movie from the TASVideos.org group and add it to the TASVideos-obsoletions group.
					$LF
				]li
			]ul
		]div
		[div class=tab-pane fade id=tabs-3371-3 
			[p 
				"archive.org normally post-processes MP4s/MKVs into a streamable "512kb" encode, which is automatically linked to from the site if the archive.org link is added as a mirror.  Unfortunately, archive.org normally does a very poor job of deriving these encodes, so you may need to provide your own.  Consult 
				(__wikiLink|/EncodingGuide/StreamingMedia|EncodingGuide/StreamingMedia)
				" for information about what is needed for this.
				$LF
			]p
		]div
